- AC/DC — Who Made Who: The candidate is described as riff‑driven hard rock with punchy, upfront guitars, tight drums and bass, concise 3–5 minute songs, and “raw‑but‑clear” production that preserves transients and guitar heft. It explicitly calls out strong sequencing and preserved dynamic range that reward album‑length listening. Those attributes match my stated love of guitar‑forward classic rock, immersive mixes that retain transients and heft, and albums that hang together as a unified, start‑to‑finish experience.
