I choose AC/DC — Who Made Who. The decisive factors are genre, arrangement focus, and album cohesion. My primary listening preference is album‑oriented, guitar‑driven classic rock/AOR with immersive mixes that retain analog character and dynamics. The AC/DC candidate is explicitly riff‑forward, guitar‑centric, and described as having raw‑but‑clear production that preserves transients and heft — exactly the kind of sonic signature I prize. It also claims strong sequencing and dynamic range that reward listening to the disc as a unified journey, matching my habit of playing physical CDs from start to finish and enjoying the album experience, not just singles.
