Conclusion: The riff‑driven hard rock CD aligns more comprehensively with my priorities—preserved dynamics, guitar‑forward mixes, strong sequencing and a visceral listening experience—while the Reprise anthology, despite good mastering and cohesion, leans into orchestral, vocal‑centered textures that conflict with my core tastes.

